Package: gretaR
Title: Bayesian Statistical Modelling with Torch
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Max", "Moldovan", , "max.moldovan@adelaide.edu.au",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9680-8474"))
Description: A probabilistic programming package for Bayesian statistical
    modelling in R using native R syntax. Models are defined interactively
    with 'gretaR_array' objects, then compiled to 'torch' tensors for
    GPU-accelerated Hamiltonian Monte Carlo and No-U-Turn Sampler inference.
    No Python dependency required.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/max578/gretaR
